Resource : aws_lb

aws_alb is know as aws_lb 

Example : Application LoadBalancer 

resource " aws_lb" "test"{
  name= "aws_alb"
  internal = false
  load_balancer_type = "application"
  security_groups = [var.security_group]
  subnets = [var.subnets]
 
  enable_deletion_protection = true
  access_logs {
    bucket = var.bucket
    prefix = "alb_bucket"
    enable = true
  }
  tags = {
    Environment = "production "
  }
}

Example: Network Load balancer 

resource "aws_lb" "this"{
  name = "aws_nlb"
  internal = false
  load_balancer_type= "network"
  subnets = var.subnets_ids
  enable_deletion_protection = true
  tags {
    Environment = "production"


}


Example :  subnet mapping 

resource "aws_lb" "example"{
  name = "example"
  load_balancer_type = "network"

  subnet_mapping {
    subnet_id  = var.subnet_id
    allocation_id= var.eip_id
  }
  subnet_mapping {
    subnet_id = var.subnets2_id
    allocation_id = var.eip2_id
  }
}

 

Specifying the private ip addresss for an internal-facing load_balaner 
the subnet mapping is only done for the nlb 

resource "aws_lb" "example"{
  name = "example"
  load_balaner_type = "network"
  internal = true
   
  subnet_mapping {
    subnet_id = var.subnet1_id
    private_ipv4_address = "10.0.1.15"
  }
  subnet_mapping {
    subnet_id =var.subnet2_id
    private_ipv4_address = "10.0.2.15"
  }
}

Core Required Arguments 

load_balancer_type = "application" or "network"

subents = var.public_subnets
subent_mapping {
  subnet_id = var.subnet1
  private_ipv4_address= "10.0.1.15"
}


name = "prod-alb"


internal = false # public LB
internal = true # private LB


Networking and traffic control

security_groups = [aws_security_groups.alb_sg.id]  # controls who can access the lb
ip_address_type = "ipv4" or "dualstack" # ivp4 default


enable_cross_zone_load_balancing =true  
# Important for the network loadbalancers
# Meaning traffic can go across AZs improve load distribution

dns_record_client_routing_policy = "any_availability_zone"

any_availability_zone = send traffic anywhere
availability_zone_affinity = stick to the same AZ
partial_availability_zone_affinity = try local first ,else go anywhere
Policy	Behavior
any_availability_zone	Route to ANY AZ
availability_zone_affinity	Prefer same AZ as client
partial_availability_zone_affinity	Prefer local AZ, fallback to others



